cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper deals with flocking dynamics of multiple agents and proposes a control law for the same. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The proposed control law is implemented using model-predictive control (MPC), which is commonly used in robotics. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with control of a system of multiple agents and proposes a control law for the same. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a new approach for flocking dynamics, which can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with the behavior of a network of agents and proposes a control law for the same.
